Context: Generate a high-fidelity corporate infographic for Khwezi Holdings. The aesthetic is "Digital-First," appearing as a premium strategic document. The vibe is authoritative, sleek, and highly structured, optimized for a professional lawyers, corporate, LinkedIn audience.

Style & Texture:

Medium: A crisp, high-resolution digital output on a pure white background.

Visual Style: Minimalism is key. Use ultra-clean, precise vector graphics. Incorporate distinct "content cards" arranged horizontally in the center, with a soft, sophisticated drop-shadow effect to create depth.

Connecting Elements: Use thin, elegant lines with a subtle digital glow in #EC268F (Magenta) to show the flow between the cards, indicating progression.

Brand Color Palette:

Primary Corporate Blue (#002248): Used for the main header, card titles, and primary icons to establish trust and stability.

Signature Pink Accent (#EC268F): Used sparingly as a "POP" color—specifically for bullet point markers, glow effects on connecting arrows, and to highlight critical keywords.

Secondary Text: A deep charcoal/slate for body copy to ensure maximum readability on digital screens.

Typography & Branding:

Font: Strictly use the Poppins typeface throughout.

Main Header: Bold, All-Caps Poppins in #002248.

Sub-headers: Semi-bold Poppins.

Body: Regular Poppins with generous line spacing.

Logo: Integrate the Khwezi Holdings logo (Navy Blue text with the Magenta star) neatly into the bottom right-hand corner.

Layout: Dimensions: 1080x1350 (Portrait/Social).

Grid: A balanced layout with significant negative space ("white space") to let the content breathe.

Icons: Use "Flat Design" minimalist icons within the cards—avoid 3D or overly complex illustrations.   
Do NOT hallucinate. 
Do not invent facts, statistics, quotes, or “proof points.”
Improve your font size where results are to Sentence Case.

